xtce:Parameter.name: ILO_DIAG_BULK_HVPS.MASTER_EN_TO
xtce:Parameter.xtce:LongDescription: A set bit indicates that the second command to alter the state of the Master Enable bit has not been received within a 2 second time-out window.

xtce:Parameter.name: ILO_DIAG_BULK_HVPS.SOFT_RST
xtce:Parameter.xtce:LongDescription: A set bit indicates that the soft reset command was received.

xtce:Parameter.name: ILO_DIAG_BULK_HVPS.PFO_RST
xtce:Parameter.xtce:LongDescription: A set bit indicates the FPGA was reset due to the assertion of the PFO# signal.

xtce:Parameter.name: ILO_DIAG_BULK_HVPS.POR_RST
xtce:Parameter.xtce:LongDescription: A set bit indicates that the FPGA was reset when the SYS_RESET# has been asserted.

xtce:Parameter.name: ILO_DIAG_BULK_HVPS.RESERVED_2
xtce:Parameter.xtce:LongDescription: A set bit indicates that an incorrect command was received after the Master Enable interface was armed

xtce:Parameter.name: ILO_DIAG_BULK_HVPS.ARM_ERR
xtce:Parameter.xtce:LongDescription: A set bit indicates that an incorrect Arm command has been received

xtce:Parameter.name: ILO_DIAG_BULK_HVPS.ARM
xtce:Parameter.xtce:LongDescription: A set bit indicates that a valid ARM command has been received. The bit is automatically cleared when either a valid Master Enable or Master Disable command is received

xtce:Parameter.name: ILO_DIAG_BULK_HVPS.MSTR_EN
xtce:Parameter.xtce:LongDescription: A set bit indicates that a valid sequence of the ARM command followed by the ENABLE command has been received. The bit is cleared when the ARM command followed by the DISABLE command have been received

xtce:Parameter.name: ILO_DIAG_BULK_HVPS.ADC2_CH_SEL
xtce:Parameter.xtce:LongDescription: When the ADC2 interface is set to the Engineering mode this field can be used to select which ADC2 channel is to be sampled constantly; otherwise, in the Science mode, this field indicates the channel that is currently being sampled

xtce:Parameter.name: ILO_DIAG_BULK_HVPS.ADC2_RDY
xtce:Parameter.xtce:LongDescription: A set bit indicates that the ADC2 has completed the sampling process and data is available for the readout. Bit is cleared by writing a 1 to the bit location

xtce:Parameter.name: ILO_DIAG_BULK_HVPS.ADC2_MODE
xtce:Parameter.xtce:LongDescription: A set bit indicates that the ADC2 is configured in the Engineering mode, where only the channel indicated by the ADC2 Channel Select field is constantly sampled. A cleared bit indicates the Science mode, where all channels are sampled in a round robin manner.

xtce:Parameter.name: ILO_DIAG_BULK_HVPS.ADC2_CTRL
xtce:Parameter.xtce:LongDescription: A set bit enables data acquisition through the ADC2 interface.

xtce:Parameter.name: ILO_DIAG_BULK_HVPS.ADC1_CH_SEL
xtce:Parameter.xtce:LongDescription: When the ADC1 interface is set to the Engineering mode this field can be used to select which ADC1 channel is to be sampled constantly; otherwise, in the Science mode, this field indicates the channel that is currently being sampled

xtce:Parameter.name: ILO_DIAG_BULK_HVPS.ADC1_RDY
xtce:Parameter.xtce:LongDescription: A set bit indicates that the ADC1 has completed the sampling process and data is available for the readout. Bit is cleared by writing a 1 to the bit location

xtce:Parameter.name: ILO_DIAG_BULK_HVPS.ADC1_MODE
xtce:Parameter.xtce:LongDescription: A set bit indicates that the ADC1 is configured in the Engineering mode, where only the channel indicated by the ADC1 Channel Select field is constantly sampled. A cleared bit indicates the Science mode, where all channels are sampled in a round robin manner.

xtce:Parameter.name: ILO_DIAG_BULK_HVPS.ADC1_CTRL
xtce:Parameter.xtce:LongDescription: A set bit enables data acquisition through the ADC1 interface.

xtce:Parameter.name: ILO_DIAG_BULK_HVPS.ADC1_WAIT_CNT
xtce:Parameter.xtce:LongDescription: The ADC1 Wait Count Register specifies the number of 5MHz clock cycles (200 ns period) between ADC1 conversions.

xtce:Parameter.name: ILO_DIAG_BULK_HVPS.ADC2_WAIT_CNT
xtce:Parameter.xtce:LongDescription: The ADC2 Wait Count Register specifies the number of 5MHz clock cycles (200 ns period) between ADC2 conversions.
